docs.notes:
Zack is the Artist Liaison for the Lyrics & Laughter Stage and will be your main contact on site. He will meet you when you arrive with your credential package and show you to your stage.

Credentials:
Each band and crew member will receive an artist laminate that will allow you access to the festival and the backstage area of your stage. 

You will be able to pull up to a specified loading area to unload/load any gear and then will need to park in our offsite parking lot. Our offsite parking area is about a mile from the site. We will assist in transportation from and to, if available. We encourage, if you can, to take alternative transportation to the festival.

Please note that a portion of I 85 is closed in both directions between the I 75 split and SR400. Attached are suggested alternate routes if you are driving southbound to the festival. Please take some time to plan your route to ensure on time arrival for your load in.

Settlement:
Settlement will be made in cash on the day of the show.

Dressing Room and hospitality: 
You will have access to a communal backstage tent for all artists performing on the stage that day.  

General hospitality will be provided - pita, hummus, pretzels, fruit, candy, water, sodas and an assortment of SweetWater 420 beer. 

Wifi Network and Password will be available in green room area.

docs.name: Paste In-Studio
docs.parking:
We're a few blocks south of Penn Station and MSG at 350 7th ave., Suite 500, New York, NY 10001. No security list at the door, just come up to the 5th floor and turn left.

Parking is very tough, please leave ample time. There is a lot around the corner on 29th between 7th and 8th, but they won't take 15 passenger vans or anything with a trailer. If you have a large vehicle or a trailer, it's street parking only.
docs.notes:
3 songs is ideal. Sessions usually take 60 minutes, sometimes up to 90 depending on complexity of instrumentation/setup.

The band is welcome to setup any way they choose, but please let them know that there are no / monitors / PA / backline here, so acoustic or light electric arrangements tend to work best. An arrangement where they can comfortably hear themselves in the room without the help of a monitor speaker is ideal.

We're on the 5th floor of an office building, large gear is problematic to load into the passenger elevators. If large gear must be loaded in, please load-in via the freight elevator (coordinate with me or Bob, we're happy to assist). The entrance is on W 29th btw 7th & 8th, one door down from the Indian restaurant at 205 W 29th St, New York, NY 10001. Freight hours are 8am-4pm, closed for lunch between noon-1pm.

We have no backline gear here apart from three nice Epiphone acoustic guitars which the band is welcome to use.

We stream these in realtime via FB Live and publish to PasteMagazine.com within a week of performance date.

docs.name: Motorco Music Hall
docs.parking:
Motorco Music Hall is on the corner of Rigsbee Ave. and Geer St. in Durham. You can park band vehicles next to the building along Geer St. where you see the long line of giant windows.
For bus arrival, you are best to drive in from the East(heading west) on Geer St. and pull over the curb. This will allow for a easy load in and departure. Please see attached pic for parking location. Also please do not block the staircase. We will get a fine from the Fire Marshall.
docs.notes:
We try to provide as much in-house as possible as we have an in-house restaurant for meals and snacks and two bars that include a lot of beverage options.

MEALS:
Our in-house restaurant, Parts & Labor, will handle meals. If you like, you can review the menu here (it’s good!): http://motorcomusic.com/partslabor/.  We request that you order your food from the venue side and have it delivered to you - you can then take it to Parts & Labor to eat if you like (it’s just that soundcheck normally correlates with the busy-period of the restaurant so this gets you your food faster AND takes a little pressure off of the servers.)

SNACKS
We also use the restaurant to provide fresh snacks for the band for the green room.

BEVERAGES
For drinks, we can either do beer in the green room OR tokens for drinks. Due to NC liquor laws, liquor needs to served at the bar via drink tokens.

Also, we have a Spring Water dispenser in the dressing room that we use instead of bottled water, fyi.

-Green Room: 
Small w/private bathroom next to stage. No Shower(This is generally reserved for the headliner).
-Wifi motorcoguest pw: motorcomusic
-Showers and/or Laundry: no 

- Merch Rate: 85% to artist on soft goods only. 
-Lodging Deals:
Motorco Hotel Discount: Aloft: http://www.aloftdurhamdowntown.com/
Rate: $99/night (average room is $150 per night.)

Jam wristbands.

docs.parking:

Engineer. Certain venues have space for all acts to load in prior to their set, while some will require you to load
in directly before your set. Depending on your stage, there is between 30-45 minutes between each act. If you
are unable to arrive before 5:00pm and are playing at a venue in Downtown Macon, please be aware that
Cherry St (the main street) will be closed between 2nd St and MLK JR BLVD and 2nd St will be closed
between Poplar St and Cherry St and 3rd St will be closed between Cherry St. & Mulberry St. starting at
5:00pm and access will only be available via alleys.

PARKING: Once you have loaded in, please relocate your van/trailer to the designated band parking lot
located at 678 Poplar St (directly beside Barker Driver Improvement Clinic). A security guard will be onsite at

that Bragg Jam is not responsible for any loss or damage to vehicles, personal belongings, or instruments.
If you require special parking accommodations please notify the venue directly.

docs.notes:
Stage Entrance: 101 E Washington St., Greenville, SC  29601. You will enter the site from E. Washington St. & N. Spring St.  See attached map for visual reference.
 
 
Security personnel will hand over your passes at the entrance to the site. Please let security know you are entertainment for the festival when arriving and then distribute the passes to your other members as they arrive. These passes must be placed in your vehicle’s windshield immediately after entering the site.
 
 
After receiving your pass and posting it in your windshield, either park parallel by the curbs and unload OR park behind the stage and unload (this area acts as a staging area to get gear ready to move onto the stage). If you park and unload directly behind the stage, you must then move your vehicle and park in the parallel “against the curb” spots located in the backstage area.  (YOU MUST MOVE YOUR VEHICLE INTO THE DESIGNATED PARKING SPOTS AFTER YOU UNLOAD TO MAKE ROOM FOR THE NEXT BAND).
 
You will notice that your passes have Access Times printed on them. These Access Times cover from your scheduled load-in (see schedule below) to one hour after your performance. This gives you one hour to load your equipment back into your vehicle after your set then exit the site to make way for the next act. You must remove your vehicle(s) from the designated area by the time your access time ends.

LOAD IN/PARKING
Esther's is located at the intersection of Red River & 6th Streets. The public entrance to Esther's is on Red River Street. Equipment will be loaded in and out via the stage doors on 6th street

Keep in mind that navigation apps might not be aware of the street closings that will be widespread in Austin during SXSW. You will receive a map of these closings. Vehicle Travel in downtown will be very slow, plan accordingly.

Both 6th Street and Red River will be closed during the festival. You will NOT be able to park at the venue, not cross the barricades on 6th St or Red River. Gear will be unloaded by the barricades at Red River and 5th St. The venue will have a crew to assist.

You will receive maps of parking locations and entry passes at Artist Registration

Artist Parking will not accommodate oversize vehicles, but there will be designated spots for oversized vehicle parking

LOAD IN/PARKING
Load in is on the corner of W. 6th & Nueces. Load in will be on Nueces.SEE MAP ATTACHED

Though the venue is in downtown, it is not within the radius of crazy street closures, so it should be relatively smooth making your way to Little Woodrow's. That said, please still give yourself ample time to account for traffic to arrive no later than ONE HOUR before your set. We will have staff to help you load in and park vehicle if vans stack up

If there are any last minute snags- please text/call Christina at 512-917-9484
docs.notes:
SETS
Because there are 6 bands performing throughout each day, we MUST adhere to a tight schedule. Please prepare accordingly. Change-overs are 20 minutes - please. We have a loader that will help you load in and show you the to your greenroom as well. 

a) be prepared to set up and line check as quickly as possible, and 
b) be respectful of subsequent bands after your set (break down, load off quick!).

Any bleed-over from change-over into set time will be subtracted from set times. In other words, each set must end at the :40 of the hour... no exceptions!

BACKLINE
Clinton with Roadway Productions will be running sound, lights and providing backline

Backline - see the attached document. Due to time constraints, everyone must use the provided backline

HOSPITALITY
We have a greenroom which will be shared as a green room by all artists. We will have a generous spread of meal / snack options throughout the day with a band tab. You will order all drinks from the greenroom bar. Band members and crew will receive laminates upon arrival which will allow access to the green room.
**Please do not invite guests into the greenroom at any time!!!
